00:58:18,147 --> 00:58:20,513
This is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

764
00:58:20,750 --> 00:58:22,809
Put it, put it down.

765
00:58:31,594 --> 00:58:33,084
Take it easy.

766
00:58:33,763 --> 00:58:35,321
You'll be all right.

767
00:58:36,365 --> 00:58:37,957
Him? What about me?

768
00:58:38,167 --> 00:58:40,567
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

769
00:58:40,770 --> 00:58:42,670
You've had worse from shaving.

770
00:58:42,872 --> 00:58:44,965
What did you do to set him off?

771
00:58:45,174 --> 00:58:47,404
Nothing.
I come in here to say farewell.

772
00:58:48,010 --> 00:58:50,672
Ain't you heard?
His parole's come through.

773
00:58:53,015 --> 00:58:55,813
I just don't understand
what happened in there.

774
00:58:56,018 --> 00:58:58,816
Old man's crazy as a rat
in a tin shithouse.

775
00:58:59,021 --> 00:59:00,921
That's enough out of you.

776
00:59:01,124 --> 00:59:03,854
- Heard he had you shitting your pants.
- Fuck you.

777
00:59:04,127 --> 00:59:05,321
IKnock it off.

778
00:59:06,295 --> 00:59:07,728
Brooks ain't no bug.

779
00:59:11,567 --> 00:59:13,330
He's just institutionalized.

780
00:59:14,704 --> 00:59:16,638
"Institutionalized," my ass.

781
00:59:16,839 --> 00:59:20,832
The man's been in here 50 years,
Heywood, 50 years!

782
00:59:21,043 --> 00:59:22,772
This is all he knows.

783
00:59:22,979 --> 00:59:25,277
In here, he's an important man...

784
00:59:25,481 --> 00:59:26,573
...an educated man.

785
00:59:27,383 --> 00:59:29,317
Outside, he's nothing.

786
00:59:30,186 --> 00:59:33,678
Just a used-up con
with arthritis in both hands.

787
00:59:33,890 --> 00:59:36,882
Probably couldn't get a library card
if he tried.

788
00:59:37,160 --> 00:59:38,889
You know what I'm trying to say?

789
00:59:39,162 --> 00:59:42,063
I do believe
you're talking out of your ass.

790
00:59:43,332 --> 00:59:45,562
You believe whatever you want.

791
00:59:46,169 --> 00:59:48,569
But I tell you these walls are funny.

792
00:59:50,173 --> 00:59:51,834
First you hate them.

793
00:59:53,676 --> 00:59:55,576
Then you get used to them.

794
00:59:57,513 --> 00:59:59,504
Enough time passes...

795
01:00:00,183 --> 01:00:02,174
...you get so you depend on them.

796
01:00:03,186 --> 01:00:05,381
That's "institutionalized."

797
01:00:05,588 --> 01:00:06,885
Shit.

798
01:00:07,089 --> 01:00:09,853
- I could never get like that.
- Oh, yeah?

799
01:00:10,726 --> 01:00:13,217
Wait till you've been here
as long as Brooks.

800
01:00:13,462 --> 01:00:15,020
Goddamn right.

801
01:00:17,600 --> 01:00:19,534
They send you here for life...

802
01:00:20,203 --> 01:00:22,535
...that's exactly what they take.

803
01:00:24,273 --> 01:00:26,264
Part that counts, anyway.

804
01:00:33,883 --> 01:00:36,818
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

805
01:00:37,987 --> 01:00:39,648
You go on now.

806
01:00:40,890 --> 01:00:42,380
You're free.

807
01:00:43,659 --> 01:00:45,217
You're free.

808
01:01:04,247 --> 01:01:05,908
Good luck, Brooksie.

809
01:01:43,886 --> 01:01:45,376
Dear fellas:

810
01:01:45,655 --> 01:01:49,853
I can't believe how fast things move
on the outside.

811
01:01:51,160 --> 01:01:53,822
Watch it, old-timer!
Want to get killed?

812
01:01:55,064 --> 01:01:58,556
I saw an automobile once
when I was a kid...

813
01:01:59,201 --> 01:02:01,635
... but now they're everywhere.

814
01:02:05,308 --> 01:02:09,608
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

815
01:02:25,428 --> 01:02:29,194
The parole board
got me into this halfway house...

816
01:02:29,498 --> 01:02:31,159
... called "The Brewster"...

817
01:02:31,367 --> 01:02:32,527
... and a job...

818
01:02:32,735 --> 01:02:35,704
... bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

819
01:02:37,239 --> 01:02:39,673
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

820
01:02:39,875 --> 01:02:42,241
... but my hands hurt most of the time.

821
01:02:42,545 --> 01:02:44,513
Make sure your man double-bags.

822
01:02:44,714 --> 01:02:46,739
Last time, the bottom near came out.

823
01:02:47,416 --> 01:02:50,351
Make sure you double-bag
like the lady says. Understand?

824
01:02:50,553 --> 01:02:51,918
Yes, sir. Surely will.

825
01:02:52,121 --> 01:02:55,648
I don't think the store manager
likes me very much.

826
01:02:58,661 --> 01:03:02,961
Sometimes after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

827
01:03:03,399 --> 01:03:04,889
I keep thinking...

828
01:03:05,134 --> 01:03:08,467
... Jake might just show up
and say hello.

829
01:03:09,071 --> 01:03:11,062
But he never does.

830
01:03:12,274 --> 01:03:17,143
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay
and making new friends.

831
01:03:20,750 --> 01:03:23,480
I have trouble sleeping at night.

832
01:03:23,786 --> 01:03:27,051
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.

833
01:03:27,323 --> 01:03:29,553
I wake up scared.

834
01:03:29,759 --> 01:03:33,991
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

835
01:03:35,498 --> 01:03:40,401
Maybe I should get a gun and rob
the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

836
01:03:40,703 --> 01:03:45,037
I could shoot the manager while
I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

837
01:03:46,709 --> 01:03:50,702
I guess I'm too old
for that sort of nonsense anymore.

838
01:03:50,946 --> 01:03:52,675
I don't like it here.

839
01:03:52,882 --> 01:03:56,875
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.
I've decided...

840
01:03:57,720 --> 01:03:59,381
... not to stay.

841
01:04:10,299 --> 01:04:12,859
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

842
01:04:13,068 --> 01:04:16,560
... not for an old crook like me.

843
01:05:19,034 --> 01:05:23,300
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss,
not for an old crook like me.

844
01:05:24,340 --> 01:05:28,174
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry
I put a knife to his throat.

845
01:05:28,377 --> 01:05:30,709
No hard feelings. Brooks."

846
01:05:41,190 --> 01:05:43,158
He should have died in here.

847
01:05:48,697 --> 01:05:50,096
What the fuck have you done?

848
01:05:50,299 --> 01:05:52,961
It's a goddamn mess,
I'll tell you that.

849
01:05:58,507 --> 01:06:02,238
- What's all this?
- You tell me. They're addressed to you.

850
01:06:03,512 --> 01:06:04,843
Take it.

851
01:06:13,389 --> 01:06:14,879
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

852
01:06:16,025 --> 01:06:17,993
In response to your inquiries...

853
01:06:18,193 --> 01:06:22,459
...the state has allocated the enclosed
funds for your library project."

854
01:06:23,232 --> 01:06:25,063
This is $ 200.

855
01:06:25,267 --> 01:06:29,260
"In addition, the library district
has generously responded...

856
01:06:29,471 --> 01:06:32,031
...with a donation of used books
and sundries.

857
01:06:32,241 --> 01:06:36,371
We trust this will fill your needs.
We now consider the matter closed.

858
01:06:36,579 --> 01:06:38,376
Please stop sending us letters."

859
01:06:38,614 --> 01:06:41,276
Clear all this out
before the warden gets back.

860
01:06:41,517 --> 01:06:42,677
Yes, sir.

861
01:06:46,956 --> 01:06:48,116
Good for you, Andy.

862
01:06:51,093 --> 01:06:52,219
Wow!

863
01:06:53,429 --> 01:06:55,363
It only took six years.

864
01:06:56,932 --> 01:06:59,662
From now on, I'll write two
letters a week instead of one.

865
01:06:59,868 --> 01:07:03,201
I believe you're crazy enough.
Get this stuff out...

866
01:07:03,472 --> 01:07:04,302
...like he said.

867
01:07:04,506 --> 01:07:05,905
I've got to pinch a loaf.

868
01:07:06,108 --> 01:07:07,575
When I come back...

869
01:07:07,776 --> 01:07:09,539
...this is all gone, all right?

870
01:07:58,293 --> 01:07:59,692
Do you hear that?

871
01:09:08,430 --> 01:09:09,590
Dufresne!

872
01:09:12,134 --> 01:09:13,658
Andy, let me out!

873
01:09:20,542 --> 01:09:25,479
I have no idea to this day what those
two Italian ladies were singing about.

874
01:09:25,781 --> 01:09:28,011
Truth is, I don't want to know.

875
01:09:28,217 --> 01:09:30,708
Some things are best left unsaid.

876
01:09:34,289 --> 01:09:37,019
I like to think it was something
so beautiful...

877
01:09:37,226 --> 01:09:39,353
... it can't be expressed in words...

878
01:09:39,561 --> 01:09:42,462
... and makes your heart ache
because of it.

879
01:09:44,133 --> 01:09:46,624
I tell you, those voices soared...

880
01:09:46,902 --> 01:09:51,202
... higher and farther than anybody
in a gray place dares to dream.

881
01:09:51,406 --> 01:09:54,773
It was like a beautiful bird
flapped into our drab cage...

882
01:09:54,977 --> 01:09:57,741
... and made those walls dissolve away.

883
01:09:58,180 --> 01:10:00,375
And for the briefest of moments...

884
01:10:00,582 --> 01:10:03,574
... every last man at Shawshank
felt free.

885
01:10:06,155 --> 01:10:08,817
It pissed the warden off
something awful.

886
01:10:10,125 --> 01:10:11,114
Open the door.

887
01:10:14,029 --> 01:10:15,792
Open it up!

888
01:10:17,099 --> 01:10:19,829
Dufresne, open this door!

889
01:10:21,170 --> 01:10:22,364
Turn that off!

890
01:10:29,444 --> 01:10:31,878
I am warning you. Turn that off!

891
01:10:49,631 --> 01:10:51,155
You're mine now.

892
01:10:58,607 --> 01:11:01,838
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

893
01:11:02,044 --> 01:11:03,636
On your feet.

894
01:11:04,813 --> 01:11:07,213
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

895
01:11:08,984 --> 01:11:12,647
You couldn't play something good, huh?
Like Hank Williams?

896
01:11:12,988 --> 01:11:15,786
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

897
01:11:15,991 --> 01:11:19,119
- Was it worth two weeks?
- Easiest time I ever did.

898
01:11:19,328 --> 01:11:23,526
- No such thing as easy time in the hole.
- A week in the hole is like a year.

899
01:11:23,732 --> 01:11:27,031
- Damn straight.
- I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

900
01:11:27,236 --> 01:11:30,205
So they let you tote
that record player down there, huh?

901
01:11:32,641 --> 01:11:34,006
It was in here.

902
01:11:34,843 --> 01:11:36,071
In here.

903
01:11:37,212 --> 01:11:39,305
That's the beauty of music. They...

904
01:11:39,514 --> 01:11:41,846
...can't get that from you.

905
01:11:45,387 --> 01:11:47,753
Haven't you ever felt
that way about music?

906
01:11:49,558 --> 01:11:52,686
Well, I played a mean harmonica
as a younger man.

907
01:11:53,729 --> 01:11:55,424
Lost interest in it, though.

908
01:11:55,631 --> 01:11:57,223
Didn't make much sense in here.

909
01:11:57,566 --> 01:11:59,557
Here's where it makes the most sense.

910
01:12:00,102 --> 01:12:02,161
You need it so you don't forget.

911
01:12:02,738 --> 01:12:03,932
Forget?

912
01:12:04,306 --> 01:12:07,400
Forget that there are...

913
01:12:07,609 --> 01:12:09,042
...places...

914
01:12:09,544 --> 01:12:13,378
...in the world
that aren't made out of stone.

915
01:12:14,383 --> 01:12:15,873
There's something...

916
01:12:16,218 --> 01:12:17,617
...inside...

917
01:12:17,886 --> 01:12:19,854
...that they can't get to...

918
01:12:20,055 --> 01:12:21,420
...that they can't touch.

919
01:12:21,957 --> 01:12:23,390
That's yours.

920
01:12:24,927 --> 01:12:26,519
What are you talking about?

921
01:12:27,562 --> 01:12:28,790
Hope.

922
01:12:29,865 --> 01:12:31,196
Hope.

923
01:12:33,135 --> 01:12:35,126
Let me tell you something, my friend.

924
01:12:35,938 --> 01:12:38,236
Hope is a dangerous thing.

925
01:12:39,408 --> 01:12:41,740
Hope can drive a man insane.

926
01:12:42,477 --> 01:12:44,604
It's got no use on the inside.

927
01:12:44,813 --> 01:12:47,008
You'd better get used to that idea.

928
01:12:49,518 --> 01:12:51,008
Like Brooks did?

929
01:13:16,378 --> 01:13:17,367
Sit down.

930
01:13:22,718 --> 01:13:26,017
Says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

931
01:13:27,189 --> 01:13:29,248
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

932
01:13:29,458 --> 01:13:30,686
Oh, yes, sir.

933
01:13:31,960 --> 01:13:33,291
Without a doubt.

934
01:13:34,463 --> 01:13:36,863
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

935
01:13:38,867 --> 01:13:40,801
No danger to society here.

936
01:13:41,336 --> 01:13:42,860
God's honest truth.

937
01:13:45,440 --> 01:13:47,533
Absolutely rehabilitated.

938
01:13:57,517 --> 01:13:58,848
Thirty years.

939
01:14:00,820 --> 01:14:02,720
Jesus, when you say it like that...

940
01:14:03,589 --> 01:14:05,386
You wonder where it went.

941
01:14:07,827 --> 01:14:09,988
I wonder where 10 years went.

942
01:14:14,967 --> 01:14:15,991
Here.

943
01:14:16,435 --> 01:14:19,165
A little parole rejection present.

944
01:14:20,439 --> 01:14:22,134
Go ahead and open it.

945
01:14:23,242 --> 01:14:25,267
Went through one of your competitors.

946
01:14:25,478 --> 01:14:28,606
I hope you don't mind.
I wanted it to be a surprise.

947
01:14:38,658 --> 01:14:40,148
It's very pretty.

948
01:14:41,861 --> 01:14:43,055
Thank you.

949
01:14:45,631 --> 01:14:47,098
You going to play it?

950
01:14:51,671 --> 01:14:52,933
No.

951
01:14:56,542 --> 01:14:57,941
Not right now.

952
01:15:15,628 --> 01:15:16,720
Roll in!

953
01:15:52,932 --> 01:15:54,160
Lights out!

954
01:16:28,768 --> 01:16:30,895
Andy was as good as his word.

955
01:16:31,270 --> 01:16:34,034
He wrote two letters a week
instead of one.

956
01:16:36,108 --> 01:16:40,204
In 1959, the state senate
finally clued in to the fact...

957
01:16:40,446 --> 01:16:43,574
... they couldn't buy him off
with just a $ 200 check.

958
01:16:43,783 --> 01:16:48,083
Appropriations Committee
voted an annual payment of $500...

959
01:16:48,287 --> 01:16:50,187
... just to shut him up.

960
01:16:50,389 --> 01:16:53,381
And you'd be amazed how far
Andy could stretch it.

961
01:16:53,592 --> 01:16:56,527
He made deals with book clubs,
charity groups.

962
01:16:56,729 --> 01:16:59,493
He bought remaindered books
by the pound...

963
01:16:59,999 --> 01:17:01,523
Treasure Island.

964
01:17:02,068 --> 01:17:03,399
Robert Louis...

965
01:17:03,602 --> 01:17:04,626
Stevenson.

966
01:17:04,837 --> 01:17:06,202
Fiction, adventure.

967
01:17:08,774 --> 01:17:09,798
What's next?

968
01:17:10,009 --> 01:17:13,069
I got here Auto Repair...

969
01:17:13,813 --> 01:17:14,973
...and Soap Carving.

970
01:17:15,181 --> 01:17:18,412
Trade skills and hobbies.
Under "Educational," behind you.

971
01:17:18,617 --> 01:17:20,482
Count of Monte Crisco.

972
01:17:20,953 --> 01:17:23,251
That's "Cristo," you dumb shit.

973
01:17:24,356 --> 01:17:25,345
By Alexandree...

974
01:17:25,825 --> 01:17:27,087
...Dum-ass.

975
01:17:27,426 --> 01:17:28,450
Dumb ass.

976
01:17:30,763 --> 01:17:31,821
Dumb ass?

977
01:17:34,734 --> 01:17:36,702
Dumas. IKnow what that's about?

978
01:17:38,971 --> 01:17:40,939
You'd like it.
It's about a prison break.

979
01:17:41,140 --> 01:17:45,042
We ought to file that
under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?

980
01:17:45,911 --> 01:17:50,007
The rest of us did our best
to pitch in when and where we could.

981
01:17:50,583 --> 01:17:52,346
By the year Kennedy was shot...

982
01:17:52,585 --> 01:17:57,079
... Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of turpentine...

983
01:17:57,389 --> 01:18:00,483
... into the best prison library
in New England...

984
01:18:01,193 --> 01:18:04,128
... complete with a fine selection
of Hank Williams.

985
01:18:11,504 --> 01:18:13,438
That was also when Warden Norton...

986
01:18:13,639 --> 01:18:16,574
... instituted his famous
"Inside Out" program.

987
01:18:17,042 --> 01:18:19,101
You may remember reading about it.

988
01:18:19,345 --> 01:18:22,439
It made the papers
and got his picture in Look magazine.

989
01:18:22,648 --> 01:18:23,945
It's no free ride...

990
01:18:24,150 --> 01:18:27,381
...but rather a genuine
progressive advance...

991
01:18:27,586 --> 01:18:30,077
...in corrections and rehabilitation.

992
01:18:30,422 --> 01:18:32,947
Our inmates, properly supervised...

993
01:18:33,159 --> 01:18:35,787
...will be put to work
outside these walls...

994
01:18:35,995 --> 01:18:39,556
...performing all manner
of public service.

995
01:18:39,832 --> 01:18:42,062
These men can learn the value...

996
01:18:42,268 --> 01:18:46,068
...of an honest day's labor and
provide a service to the community...

997
01:18:46,272 --> 01:18:50,971
...at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. And Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.

998
01:18:51,410 --> 01:18:53,742
Of course he didn't tell the press...

999
01:18:53,946 --> 01:18:57,404
... that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

1000
01:18:57,616 --> 01:19:00,642
There are 100 different ways
to skim off the top.

1001
01:19:00,853 --> 01:19:03,344
Men, materials, you name it.

1002
01:19:03,689 --> 01:19:06,590
And oh, my Lord,
how the money rolled in!

1003
01:19:06,792 --> 01:19:09,317
At this rate,
you'll put me out of business.

1004
01:19:09,528 --> 01:19:13,965
With this pool of slave labor,
you can underbid any contractor in town.

1005
01:19:14,533 --> 01:19:17,502
We're providing
a valuable community service.

1006
01:19:17,703 --> 01:19:21,366
That's fine for the papers,
but I've got a family to feed.

1007
01:19:24,043 --> 01:19:25,567
We go back a long way.

1008
01:19:26,879 --> 01:19:31,816
I need this highway contract. I don't
get it and I go under. That's a fact.

1009
01:19:32,718 --> 01:19:34,515
You have some of this fine pie...

1010
01:19:34,753 --> 01:19:38,086
...my missus made for you.
You think about that.

1011
01:19:46,365 --> 01:19:49,061
I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

1012
01:19:49,301 --> 01:19:52,361
I already got my boys
committed elsewhere.

1013
01:19:54,340 --> 01:19:57,400
You be sure and thank Maisie
for this fine pie.

1014
01:19:58,510 --> 01:20:00,671
And behind every shady deal...

1015
01:20:01,013 --> 01:20:03,641
... behind every dollar earned...

1016
01:20:03,916 --> 01:20:06,976
... there was Andy, keeping the books.

1017
01:20:07,386 --> 01:20:08,648
Two deposits.

