Board of Education.

1263
01:34:39,090 --> 01:34:40,614
That son of a bitch mailed it.

1264
01:34:40,825 --> 01:34:44,784
You going to open it or stand there
with your thumb up your butt?

1265
01:34:44,996 --> 01:34:47,157
Thumb up my butt sounds better.

1266
01:34:47,665 --> 01:34:50,498
Skeets, come on.
Give me that, you shithead.

1267
01:34:51,336 --> 01:34:52,667
Floyd, come on.

1268
01:34:58,109 --> 01:35:00,509
Will you throw that away, please?

1269
01:35:06,117 --> 01:35:07,846
Well, shit.

1270
01:35:20,532 --> 01:35:23,330
The kid passed. C + average.

1271
01:35:23,535 --> 01:35:25,628
Thought you'd like to know.

1272
01:35:41,853 --> 01:35:43,320
Warden wants to talk.

1273
01:35:57,068 --> 01:35:58,126
Out here?

1274
01:35:58,336 --> 01:36:00,566
That's what the man said.

1275
01:36:16,688 --> 01:36:17,677
Warden?

1276
01:36:27,699 --> 01:36:31,760
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

1277
01:36:33,271 --> 01:36:35,535
I feel awkward enough as it is.

1278
01:36:53,992 --> 01:36:56,051
We got a situation here.

1279
01:36:56,928 --> 01:36:59,021
I think you can appreciate that.

1280
01:36:59,230 --> 01:37:00,458
Yes, sir.

1281
01:37:00,732 --> 01:37:02,131
I sure can.

1282
01:37:02,400 --> 01:37:06,427
I tell you, son, this thing really
came along and knocked my wind out.

1283
01:37:07,906 --> 01:37:10,466
It's got me up nights.
That's the truth.

1284
01:37:12,744 --> 01:37:14,575
The right thing to do...

1285
01:37:16,247 --> 01:37:19,978
...sometimes it's hard to know
what that is.

1286
01:37:20,985 --> 01:37:22,418
Do you understand?

1287
01:37:24,722 --> 01:37:26,314
I need your help, son.

1288
01:37:27,759 --> 01:37:29,920
If I'm going to move on this...

1289
01:37:30,261 --> 01:37:33,424
...there can't be
the least little shred of doubt.

1290
01:37:34,165 --> 01:37:35,223
I have to know...

1291
01:37:35,433 --> 01:37:38,061
...if what you told Dufresne
was the truth.

1292
01:37:38,269 --> 01:37:39,395
Yes, sir.

1293
01:37:39,604 --> 01:37:40,832
Absolutely.

1294
01:37:41,339 --> 01:37:44,331
Would you be willing to swear
before a judge and jury...

1295
01:37:44,542 --> 01:37:46,533
...with your hand on the Good Book...

1296
01:37:46,744 --> 01:37:49,406
...and take an oath
before Almighty God himself?

1297
01:37:49,614 --> 01:37:51,411
Just give me that chance.

1298
01:37:55,687 --> 01:37:57,018
That's what I thought.

1299
01:38:44,102 --> 01:38:46,002
I'm sure by now you've heard.

1300
01:38:47,772 --> 01:38:48,796
Terrible thing.

1301
01:38:50,408 --> 01:38:51,875
A man that young...

1302
01:38:52,210 --> 01:38:54,804
...less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

1303
01:38:55,346 --> 01:38:57,837
Broke Captain Hadley's heart
to shoot him.

1304
01:38:58,583 --> 01:39:00,073
Truly, it did.

1305
01:39:03,087 --> 01:39:05,521
We just have to put it behind us.

1306
01:39:07,191 --> 01:39:08,419
Move on.

1307
01:39:10,028 --> 01:39:11,518
I'm done.

1308
01:39:12,830 --> 01:39:14,457
Everything stops.

1309
01:39:16,434 --> 01:39:18,766
Get someone else to run your scams.

1310
01:39:20,038 --> 01:39:21,869
Nothing stops.

1311
01:39:23,207 --> 01:39:24,367
Nothing.

1312
01:39:27,779 --> 01:39:30,873
Or you will do
the hardest time there is.

1313
01:39:31,282 --> 01:39:33,580
No more protection from the guards.

1314
01:39:33,818 --> 01:39:38,721
I'll pull you out of that 1 -bunk Hilton
and cast you down with the sodomites.

1315
01:39:40,124 --> 01:39:42,558
You'll think you've been
fucked by a train.

1316
01:39:43,961 --> 01:39:45,451
And the library?

1317
01:39:46,130 --> 01:39:47,119
Gone.

1318
01:39:47,732 --> 01:39:50,292
Sealed off, brick by brick.

1319
01:39:50,768 --> 01:39:53,430
We'll have us a little
book barbecue in the yard.

1320
01:39:53,638 --> 01:39:55,765
They'll see the flames for miles.

1321
01:39:55,973 --> 01:39:58,806
We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.

1322
01:40:00,078 --> 01:40:03,070
You understand me? Catching my drift?

1323
01:40:06,818 --> 01:40:08,683
Or am I being obtuse?

1324
01:40:20,465 --> 01:40:23,093
Give him another month
to think about it.

1325
01:41:09,847 --> 01:41:12,907
My wife used to say
I'm a hard man to know.

1326
01:41:13,718 --> 01:41:15,549
Like a closed book.

1327
01:41:16,354 --> 01:41:18,379
Complained about it all the time.

1328
01:41:19,323 --> 01:41:20,881
She was beautiful.

1329
01:41:23,294 --> 01:41:24,818
God, I loved her.

1330
01:41:28,533 --> 01:41:30,763
I didn't know how
to show it, that's all.

1331
01:41:33,504 --> 01:41:35,165
I killed her, Red.

1332
01:41:37,041 --> 01:41:38,838
I didn't pull the trigger...

1333
01:41:40,278 --> 01:41:42,007
...but I drove her away.

1334
01:41:43,514 --> 01:41:46,210
That's why she died, because of me...

1335
01:41:46,417 --> 01:41:47,782
...the way I am.

1336
01:41:56,794 --> 01:41:58,625
That don't make you a murderer.

1337
01:42:01,999 --> 01:42:03,762
Bad husband, maybe.

1338
01:42:07,405 --> 01:42:10,670
Feel bad about it if you want,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

1339
01:42:10,875 --> 01:42:12,206
No, I didn't.

1340
01:42:12,610 --> 01:42:14,544
Somebody else did.

1341
01:42:15,780 --> 01:42:17,873
And I wound up in here.

1342
01:42:20,351 --> 01:42:21,943
Bad luck, I guess.

1343
01:42:27,158 --> 01:42:28,591
It floats around.

1344
01:42:29,627 --> 01:42:31,857
It's got to land on somebody.

1345
01:42:32,763 --> 01:42:34,663
It was my turn, that's all.

1346
01:42:35,366 --> 01:42:38,130
I was in the path of the tornado.

1347
01:42:44,075 --> 01:42:48,034
I just didn't expect the storm
would last as long as it has.

1348
01:42:52,383 --> 01:42:54,078
Think you'll ever get out of here?

1349
01:42:55,319 --> 01:42:56,343
Me?

1350
01:42:59,323 --> 01:43:00,312
Yeah.

1351
01:43:01,659 --> 01:43:03,957
One day, when I got
a long, white beard...

1352
01:43:04,161 --> 01:43:07,324
...and two or three marbles
rolling around upstairs.

1353
01:43:09,367 --> 01:43:10,994
I tell you where I'd go.

1354
01:43:12,470 --> 01:43:14,131
Zihuatanejo.

1355
01:43:15,006 --> 01:43:16,200
Say what?

1356
01:43:16,507 --> 01:43:18,338
Zihuatanejo.

1357
01:43:19,277 --> 01:43:20,938
It's in Mexico.

1358
01:43:22,313 --> 01:43:24,440
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

1359
01:43:25,583 --> 01:43:28,381
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

1360
01:43:30,187 --> 01:43:32,178
They say it has no memory.

1361
01:43:34,158 --> 01:43:36,820
That's where I want to live
the rest of my life.

1362
01:43:38,462 --> 01:43:40,953
A warm place with no memory.

1363
01:43:44,201 --> 01:43:46,135
Open up a little hotel...

1364
01:43:47,838 --> 01:43:49,328
...right on the beach.

1365
01:43:49,940 --> 01:43:52,135
Buy some worthless old boat...

1366
01:43:52,677 --> 01:43:54,304
...and fix it up new.

1367
01:43:57,048 --> 01:43:58,276
Take my guests out...

1368
01:43:59,116 --> 01:44:00,481
...charter fishing.

1369
01:44:04,322 --> 01:44:06,051
Zihuatanejo.

1370
01:44:09,593 --> 01:44:13,461
In a place like that, I could use
a man that knows how to get things.

1371
01:44:20,004 --> 01:44:22,837
I don't think I could make it
on the outside.

1372
01:44:29,513 --> 01:44:31,572
I been in here most of my life.

1373
01:44:33,017 --> 01:44:34,780
I'm an institutional man now.

1374
01:44:35,686 --> 01:44:37,415
Just like Brooks was.

1375
01:44:38,889 --> 01:44:40,584
You underestimate yourself.

1376
01:44:41,158 --> 01:44:42,750
I don't think so.

1377
01:44:46,597 --> 01:44:50,533
In here I'm the guy who can get things
for you, sure, but...

1378
01:44:51,302 --> 01:44:53,827
...outside all you need
is the Yellow Pages.

1379
01:44:54,038 --> 01:44:56,268
Hell, I wouldn't know
where to begin.

1380
01:44:58,409 --> 01:45:00,036
Pacific Ocean?

1381
01:45:00,444 --> 01:45:01,672
Shit.

1382
01:45:02,046 --> 01:45:04,241
Scare me to death,
something that big.

1383
01:45:04,448 --> 01:45:05,745
Not me.

1384
01:45:06,951 --> 01:45:09,715
I didn't shoot my wife,
and I didn't shoot her lover.

1385
01:45:11,455 --> 01:45:14,686
Whatever mistakes I made,
I've paid for them and then some.

1386
01:45:15,726 --> 01:45:17,216
That hotel, that boat...

1387
01:45:18,996 --> 01:45:21,226
I don't think that's too much to ask.

1388
01:45:26,137 --> 01:45:28,571
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.

1389
01:45:28,773 --> 01:45:30,798
This is just shitty pipe dreams.

1390
01:45:31,242 --> 01:45:33,710
Mexico is way down there
and you're in here...

1391
01:45:33,911 --> 01:45:35,469
...and that's the way it is.

1392
01:45:35,813 --> 01:45:38,646
Yeah, right.
That's the way it is.

1393
01:45:40,151 --> 01:45:42,551
It's down there and I'm in here.

1394
01:45:45,122 --> 01:45:47,852
I guess it comes down
to a simple choice.

1395
01:45:50,761 --> 01:45:52,251
Get busy living...

1396
01:45:53,631 --> 01:45:55,656
...or get busy dying.

1397
01:46:07,778 --> 01:46:10,508
If you ever get out of here,
do me a favor.

1398
01:46:10,714 --> 01:46:12,978
Sure, Andy. Anything.

1399
01:46:14,852 --> 01:46:18,720
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

1400
01:46:20,191 --> 01:46:23,319
- A lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

1401
01:46:23,527 --> 01:46:27,463
It's got a long rock wall
with a big oak tree at the north end.

1402
01:46:27,665 --> 01:46:30,532
It's like something
out of a Robert Frost poem.

1403
01:46:31,469 --> 01:46:33,960
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

1404
01:46:35,372 --> 01:46:37,465
We went there for a picnic...

1405
01:46:37,875 --> 01:46:39,968
...and made love under that oak...

1406
01:46:40,644 --> 01:46:42,874
...and I asked and she said yes.

1407
01:46:46,884 --> 01:46:48,715
Promise me, Red.

1408
01:46:49,553 --> 01:46:51,180
If you ever get out...

1409
01:46:51,388 --> 01:46:52,878
...find that spot.

1410
01:46:54,058 --> 01:46:58,893
At the base of that wall, there's a rock
that has no earthly business in Maine.

1411
01:47:00,030 --> 01:47:03,056
Piece of black, volcanic glass.

1412
01:47:05,736 --> 01:47:08,398
Something's buried under it
I want you to have.

1413
01:47:09,173 --> 01:47:10,401
What, Andy?

1414
01:47:10,841 --> 01:47:12,570
What's buried under there?

1415
01:47:14,178 --> 01:47:16,043
You'll have to pry it up...

1416
01:47:16,247 --> 01:47:17,509
...to see.

1417
01:47:23,387 --> 01:47:25,355
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...

1418
01:47:26,023 --> 01:47:27,752
He's talking funny.

1419
01:47:28,859 --> 01:47:30,554
I'm really worried about him.

1420
01:47:30,961 --> 01:47:32,394
Let's keep an eye on him.

1421
01:47:32,596 --> 01:47:35,861
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's all alone.

1422
01:47:37,301 --> 01:47:38,427
Oh, Lord.

1423
01:47:39,770 --> 01:47:40,600
What?

1424
01:47:42,106 --> 01:47:44,870
Andy come down
to the loading dock today.

1425
01:47:45,075 --> 01:47:47,168
He asked me for a length of rope.

1426
01:47:47,378 --> 01:47:48,208
Rope?

1427
01:47:48,412 --> 01:47:50,073
Six feet long.

1428
01:47:50,314 --> 01:47:51,679
And you gave it to him.

1429
01:47:52,550 --> 01:47:54,347
Sure. Why wouldn't I?

1430
01:47:54,552 --> 01:47:56,110
Jesus! Heywood.

1431
01:47:56,720 --> 01:47:58,688
How was I supposed to know?

1432
01:47:58,889 --> 01:48:00,447
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

1433
01:48:02,459 --> 01:48:04,393
Andy would never do that.

1434
01:48:04,995 --> 01:48:06,053
Never.

1435
01:48:08,132 --> 01:48:09,463
I don't know.

1436
01:48:12,303 --> 01:48:14,328
Every man has his breaking point.

1437
01:48:16,674 --> 01:48:18,938
Lickety-split.
Want to get home.

1438
01:48:19,243 --> 01:48:21,006
Just about finished, sir.

1439
01:48:38,128 --> 01:48:39,755
Three deposits tonight.

1440
01:48:47,738 --> 01:48:49,638
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1441
01:48:49,840 --> 01:48:51,467
And shine my shoes.

1442
01:48:51,675 --> 01:48:54,610
- I want them looking like mirrors.
- Yes, sir.

1443
01:49:00,117 --> 01:49:01,584
It's good having you back.

1444
01:49:02,519 --> 01:49:04,384
Place wasn't the same without you.

1445
01:49:51,268 --> 01:49:52,326
Lights out!

1446
01:50:25,169 --> 01:50:27,694
I've had some long nights in stir.

1447
01:50:28,238 --> 01:50:30,900
Alone in the dark
with nothing but your thoughts...

1448
01:50:31,108 --> 01:50:33,770
... time can draw out like a blade.

1449
01:50:39,116 --> 01:50:42,108
That was the longest night of my life.

1450
01:50:57,968 --> 01:50:59,128
Give me a count!

1451
01:51:03,640 --> 01:51:06,473
Tier 3 south, clear!

1452
01:51:09,613 --> 01:51:12,776
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!

1453
01:51:12,983 --> 01:51:14,041
Dufresne!

1454
01:51:14,585 --> 01:51:17,019
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1455
01:51:20,157 --> 01:51:23,558
Don't make me come down
or I'll thump your skull for you!

1456
01:51:31,135 --> 01:51:34,969
Damn it, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

1457
01:51:35,172 --> 01:51:38,471
You'd better be sick or dead in there.
I shit you not!

1458
01:51:38,675 --> 01:51:40,006
You hear me?

1459
01:51:46,116 --> 01:51:48,209
Oh, my Holy God.

1460
01:52:05,202 --> 01:52:07,762
I want every man
on this cellblock questioned.

1461
01:52:08,205 --> 01:52:10,765
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

1462
01:52:13,343 --> 01:52:14,901
Open 237.

1463
01:52:18,415 --> 01:52:22,078
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1464
01:52:22,953 --> 01:52:24,284
Don't tell me that again.

1465
01:52:24,488 --> 01:52:25,512
But sir, he wasn't.

1466
01:52:25,756 --> 01:52:29,214
I can see that, Haig!
Think I'm blind?

1467
01:52:29,893 --> 01:52:31,292
Is that what you're saying?

1468
01:52:31,495 --> 01:52:34,157
- Am I blind, Haig?
- No, sir!

1469
01:52:35,065 --> 01:52:37,556
What about you. You blind?

1470
01:52:38,068 --> 01:52:40,628
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

1471
01:52:40,838 --> 01:52:44,137
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1472
01:52:44,341 --> 01:52:45,672
"Dufresne."

1473
01:52:47,344 --> 01:52:48,811
He was in his cell...

1474
01:52:49,046 --> 01:52:50,013
...at lights out.

1475
01:52:50,214 --> 01:52:52,478
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.

1476
01:52:53,517 --> 01:52:55,144
I want him found.

1477
01:52:55,352 --> 01:52:58,810
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1478
01:52:59,056 --> 01:53:00,250
Yes, sir.

1479
01:53:01,258 --> 01:53:03,522
Let's go. Move your butts.

1480
01:53:06,930 --> 01:53:07,919
Stand.

1481
01:53:09,366 --> 01:53:10,424
Well?

1482
01:53:13,871 --> 01:53:14,860
Well, what?

1483
01:53:15,072 --> 01:53:18,530
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1484
01:53:19,610 --> 01:53:21,100
He must have said something.

1485
01:53:21,845 --> 01:53:23,369
No, sir, Warden.

1486
01:53:23,747 --> 01:53:24,714
Not a word.

1487
01:53:26,550 --> 01:53:29,110
Lord, it's a miracle!

1488
01:53:29,720 --> 01:53:32,280
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1489
01:53:32,956 --> 01:53:34,116
Nothing left...

1490
01:53:34,958 --> 01:53:37,688
...but some damn rocks
on a windowsill.

1491
01:53:37,895 --> 01:53:40,625
And that cupcake on the wall.
Let's ask her.

1492
01:53:40,831 --> 01:53:42,594
Maybe she knows.

1493
01:53:42,833 --> 01:53:45,563
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1494
01:53:47,004 --> 01:53:48,301
Guess not.

1495
01:53:48,872 --> 01:53:51,067
Why should she be any different?

1496
01:53:52,142 --> 01:53:53,803
This is a conspiracy.

1497
01:53:54,444 --> 01:53:56,275
That's what this is.

1498
01:53:56,880 --> 01:54:00,611
One big, damn conspiracy!

1499
01:54:00,884 --> 01:54:02,875
And everyone's in on it!

1500
01:54:03,520 --> 01:54:04,680
Including her!

1501
01:54:39,723 --> 01:54:41,418
In 1966...

1502
01:54:41,625 --> 01:54:44,025
... Andy Dufresne escaped...

1503
01:54:44,227 --> 01:54:45,785
... from Shawshank Prison.

1504
01:54:48,031 --> 01:54:50,591
All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1505
01:54:51,234 --> 01:54:52,758
... a bar of soap...

1506
01:54:52,970 --> 01:54:54,528
... and an old rock hammer...

1507
01:54:54,738 --> 01:54:57,206
... damn near worn down to the nub.

1508
01:55:01,712 --> 01:55:06,479
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years
to tunnel through the wall with it.

1509
01:55:07,117 --> 01:55:09,745
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1510
01:55:28,038 --> 01:55:30,336
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1511
01:55:31,108 --> 01:55:34,271
I imagine it appealed to his
meticulous nature.

1512
01:55:34,678 --> 01:55:36,509
An ice age here...

1513
01:55:36,947 --> 01:55:39,438
... million years
of mountain building there.

1514
01:55:40,450 --> 01:55:43,283
Geology is the study
of pressure and time.

1515
01:55:44,121 --> 01:55:46,112
That's all it takes, really.

1516
01:55:46,857 --> 01:55:47,949
Pressure...

1517
01:55:48,592 --> 01:55:49,854
... and time.

1518
01:55:51,194 --> 01:55:53,253
That and a big goddamn poster.

1519
01:55:57,300 --> 01:55:58,232
Like I said...

1520
01:55:58,735 --> 01:56:02,728
... in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1521
01:56:05,542 --> 01:56:10,343
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...

1522
01:56:10,881 --> 01:56:12,815
... a handful at a time.

1523
01:56:14,117 --> 01:56:16,176
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1524
01:56:16,386 --> 01:56:19,355
... Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.

1525
01:56:19,556 --> 01:56:22,116
Lickety-split.
I want to get home.

1526
01:56:22,859 --> 01:56:24,884
I'm just about finished, sir.

1527
01:56:46,349 --> 01:56:48,283
Three deposits tonight.

1528
01:56:55,592 --> 01:56:57,890
Andy did like he was told.

1529
01:56:58,095 --> 01:57:01,587
Buffed those shoes
to a high mirror-shine.

1530
01:57:05,268 --> 01:57:07,566
The guards simply didn't notice.

1531
01:57:07,871 --> 01:57:09,338
Neither did I.

1532
01:57:09,539 --> 01:57:11,063
I mean, seriously...

1533
01:57:11,274 --> 01:57:14,266
... how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?

1534
01:59:17,834 --> 01:59:20,997
Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...

1535
01:59:21,238 --> 01:59:24,571
... of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.

1536
01:59:25,575 --> 01:59:27,907
Or maybe I just don't want to.

1537
01:59:32,315 --> 01:59:34,681
Five hundred yards.

1538
01:59:35,185 --> 01:59:38,245
That's the length
of five football fields.

1539
01:59:38,888 --> 01:59:41,448
Just shy of half a mile.

1540
02:00:36,680 --> 02:00:41,276
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...

1541
02:00:41,584 --> 02:00:44,417
... a man nobody ever
laid eyes on before...

1542
02:00:44,654 --> 02:00:47,248
... strolled into
the Maine National Bank.

1543
02:00:47,824 --> 02:00:50,987
Until that moment,
he didn't exist.

1544
02:00:51,561 --> 02:00:53,927
- Except on paper.
- May I help you?

1545
02:00:54,331 --> 02:00:56,265
He had all the proper ID...

1546
02:00:56,466 --> 02:01:00,163
... driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card...

1547
02:01:00,603 --> 02:01:03,128
And the signature
was a spot-on match.

1548
02:01:03,340 --> 02:01:06,434
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1549
02:01:06,643 --> 02:01:08,372
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1550
02:01:09,179 --> 02:01:10,271
Thank you.

1551
02:01:10,947 --> 02:01:12,107
I'm sure I will.

1552
02:01:13,016 --> 02:01:16,349
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1553
02:01:16,553 --> 02:01:17,542
Please.

1554
02:01:18,121 --> 02:01:20,612
Would you add this
to your outgoing mail?

1555
02:01:21,124 --> 02:01:22,318
I'd be happy to.

1556
02:01:24,127 --> 02:01:25,458
Good day, sir.

1557
02:01:26,396 --> 02:01:30,833
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

1558
02:01:31,301 --> 02:01:32,893
All told, he blew town...

1559
02:01:33,103 --> 02:01:37,938
... with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

1560
02:01:38,641 --> 02:01:41,405
Severance pay for 19 years.

1561
02:01:48,651 --> 02:01:50,846
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1562
02:02:43,706 --> 02:02:46,641
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1563
02:02:46,910 --> 02:02:51,347
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1564
02:02:51,781 --> 02:02:56,241
I wasn't there to see, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1565
02:02:56,453 --> 02:02:57,943
... when they took him away.

1566
02:03:03,827 --> 02:03:07,228
Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.

1567
02:03:23,079 --> 02:03:23,909
Samuel Norton.

1568
02:03:24,714 --> 02:03:27,148
We have a warrant
for your arrest. Open up.

1569
02:03:31,888 --> 02:03:32,980
Open the door.

1570
02:03:33,523 --> 02:03:34,785
I'm not sure which key.

1571
02:03:44,934 --> 02:03:46,868
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1572
02:03:58,381 --> 02:04:01,839
I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...

1573
02:04:02,051 --> 02:04:03,643
... other than that bullet...

1574
02:04:03,853 --> 02:04:08,290
... was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1575
02:04:10,793 --> 02:04:14,251
Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...

1576
02:04:14,531 --> 02:04:16,590
... I got a postcard in the mail.

1577
02:04:18,067 --> 02:04:20,900
It was blank,
but the postmark said...

1578
02:04:21,104 --> 02:04:23,231
... Fort Hancock, Texas.

1579
02:04:23,773 --> 02:04:25,138
Fort Hancock...

1580
02:04:25,408 --> 02:04:27,137
... right on the border.

1581
02:04:27,544 --> 02:04:29,535
That's where Andy crossed.

1582
02:04:30,113 --> 02:04:34,243
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...

1583
02:04:34,584 --> 02:04:36,814
... it always makes me laugh.

1584
02:04:38,655 --> 02:04:40,213
Andy Dufresne...

1585
02:04:40,590 --> 02:04:42,615
... who crawled through
a river of shit...

1586
02:04:42,825 --> 02:04:45,225
... and came out clean
on the other side.

1587
02:04:46,062 --> 02:04:47,427
Andy Dufresne...

1588
02:04:48,231 --> 02:04:49,823
... headed for the Pacific.

1589
02:04:52,802 --> 02:04:54,963
Hadley's got him
by the throat, right?

1590
02:04:55,171 --> 02:04:58,971
He says, " I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

1591
02:04:59,175 --> 02:05:02,042
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

1592
02:05:02,712 --> 02:05:04,407
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1593
02:05:04,614 --> 02:05:07,583
"My friends could use
a couple of beers."

1594
02:05:07,917 --> 02:05:09,578
And he got it!

1595
02:05:10,820 --> 02:05:13,220
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1596
02:05:13,489 --> 02:05:14,922
... Andy being gone.

1597
02:05:15,625 --> 02:05:19,755
I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1598
02:05:20,229 --> 02:05:22,288
Their feathers are just too bright.

1599
02:05:24,000 --> 02:05:25,729
And when they fly away...

1600
02:05:26,169 --> 02:05:30,572
... the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1601
02:05:31,641 --> 02:05:32,903
But still...

1602
02:05:33,376 --> 02:05:37,710
... the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.

1603
02:05:41,918 --> 02:05:44,284
I guess I just miss my friend.

1604
02:06:08,978 --> 02:06:09,910
Please sit down.

1605
02:06:15,752 --> 02:06:17,310
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1606
02:06:17,854 --> 02:06:21,119
...your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1607
02:06:21,924 --> 02:06:24,051
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1608
02:06:25,928 --> 02:06:27,486
Rehabilitated?

1609
02:06:29,532 --> 02:06:31,432
Well, now, let me see.

1610
02:06:32,435 --> 02:06:34,767
I don't have any idea
what that means.

1611
02:06:36,873 --> 02:06:39,137
It means you're ready
to rejoin society...

1612
02:06:39,709 --> 02:06:42,041
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1613
02:06:44,213 --> 02:06:46,204
To me it's just a made-up word.

1614
02:06:47,550 --> 02:06:49,882
A politician's word so that...

1615
02:06:50,319 --> 02:06:53,846
...young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1616
02:06:54,323 --> 02:06:55,915
...and have a job.

1617
02:06:57,894 --> 02:06:59,987
What do you really want to know?

1618
02:07:00,763 --> 02:07:02,731
Am I sorry for what I did?

1619
02:07:03,166 --> 02:07:04,326
Well, are you?

1620
02:07:06,235 --> 02:07:09,068
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1621
02:07:10,440 --> 02:07:13,898
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1622
02:07:17,380 --> 02:07:19,940
I look back on the way I was then...

1623
02:07:22,085 --> 02:07:23,245
...a young...

1624
02:07:24,353 --> 02:07:27,845
...stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1625
02:07:30,860 --> 02:07:32,555
I want to talk to him.

1626
02:07:34,497 --> 02:07:36,965
I want to try
and talk some sense to him.

1627
02:07:37,700 --> 02:07:39,634
Tell him the way things are.

1628
02:07:41,738 --> 02:07:43,171
But I can't.

1629
02:07:45,374 --> 02:07:47,365
That kid's long gone...

1630
02:07:48,578 --> 02:07:51,342
...and this old man is all that's left.

1631
02:07:52,749 --> 02:07:54,216
I got to live with that.

1632
02:07:55,585 --> 02:07:57,280
Rehabilitated?

1633
02:07:57,653 --> 02:07:59,484
It's just a bullshit word.

1634
02:08:00,423 --> 02:08:05,190
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1635
02:08:06,429 --> 02:08:08,693
Because to tell you the truth...

1636
02:08:09,031 --> 02:08:11,022
...I don't give a shit.

1637
02:09:37,553 --> 02:09:38,952
Here you go, miss.

1638
02:09:41,891 --> 02:09:42,915
Restroom break?

1639
02:09:48,731 --> 02:09:53,259
You don't need to ask me every time
you need to go take a piss. Just go.

1640
02:10:06,315 --> 02:10:09,375
Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.

1641
02:10:10,219 --> 02:10:13,211
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1642
02:10:16,726 --> 02:10:18,887
There's a harsh truth to face.

1643
02:10:20,563 --> 02:10:23,464
No way I'm going to make it
on the outside.

1644
02:10:31,340 --> 02:10:35,037
All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...

1645
02:10:35,845 --> 02:10:38,313
... so maybe they'd send me back.

1646
02:10:43,519 --> 02:10:45,953
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1647
02:10:46,856 --> 02:10:48,517
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1648
02:10:48,724 --> 02:10:50,658
Knew it all too well.

1649
02:10:52,261 --> 02:10:55,662
All I want is to be back
where things make sense.

1650
02:10:56,098 --> 02:10:58,828
Where I won't have to be afraid
all the time.

1651
02:11:00,836 --> 02:11:03,202
Only one thing stops me.

1652
02:11:04,640 --> 02:11:07,040
A promise I made to Andy.

1653
02:11:27,563 --> 02:11:28,689
There it is.

1654
02:11:39,308 --> 02:11:40,969
Much obliged, sir.

1655
02:15:20,296 --> 02:15:21,558
Dear Red:

1656
02:15:21,797 --> 02:15:24,265
If you're reading this,
you've gotten out...

1657
02:15:24,466 --> 02:15:28,527
... and if you've come this far,
maybe you'd come a bit further.

1658
02:15:28,804 --> 02:15:31,272
You remember the name
of the town, don't you?

1659
02:15:33,576 --> 02:15:35,066
Zihuatanejo.

1660
02:15:36,712 --> 02:15:40,307
I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.

1661
02:15:40,816 --> 02:15:44,343
I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.

1662
02:15:45,154 --> 02:15:46,553
Remember, Red...

1663
02:15:46,889 --> 02:15:48,982
... hope is a good thing...

1664
02:15:49,191 --> 02:15:51,182
... maybe the best of things.

1665
02:15:51,393 --> 02:15:53,554
And no good thing ever dies.

1666
02:15:54,096 --> 02:15:56,963
I will be hoping
that this letter finds you...

1667
02:15:57,166 --> 02:15:58,895
... and finds you well.

1668
02:15:59,401 --> 02:16:00,629
Your friend...

1669
02:16:00,836 --> 02:16:01,996
... Andy.

1670
02:16:35,838 --> 02:16:37,567
"Get busy living...

1671
02:16:37,773 --> 02:16:39,673
... or get busy dying. "

1672
02:16:42,378 --> 02:16:44,539
That's goddamn right.

1673
02:16:49,785 --> 02:16:51,912
For the second time in my life...

1674
02:16:52,154 --> 02:16:54,714
... I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1675
02:16:55,791 --> 02:16:57,725
Parole violation.

1676
02:16:58,394 --> 02:17:02,057
Of course I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

1677
02:17:02,731 --> 02:17:04,756
Not for an old crook like me.

1678
02:17:04,967 --> 02:17:06,992
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1679
02:17:10,673 --> 02:17:15,406
I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1680
02:17:15,844 --> 02:17:19,177
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

1681
02:17:19,381 --> 02:17:21,872
A free man at the start
of a long journey...

1682
02:17:22,084 --> 02:17:24,678
... whose conclusion is uncertain.

1683
02:17:27,690 --> 02:17:30,352
I hope I can make it across the border.

1684
02:17:31,860 --> 02:17:34,886
I hope to see my friend
and shake his hand.

1685
02:17:36,765 --> 02:17:40,826
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

1686
02:17:42,671 --> 02:17:43,865
I hope.

